    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <p n="1">
                    <seg n="1">Bello Alexandrino conflato Caesar Rhodo atque ex Syria Ciliciaque
                        omnem classem arcessit; 
                        <placeName
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/589748">Creta</placeName>
                        sagittarios, equites ab rege Nabataeorum Malcho euocat; tormenta undique
                        conquiri et frumentum mitti, auxilia adduci iubet.</seg>
                    <seg n="2">Interim munitiones 
                        <!-- following two apps address this: 
                            cotidie operibus] cotidie M : nouis c- o- Castiglioni
                            -->
                        <app>
                            <lem n="munitiones"/>
                            <rdg source="#Castignioni" type="conjecture-supplied">
                                <supplied reason="omitted">nouis</supplied>
                            </rdg>
                        </app> cotidie <app>
                            <lem>operibus</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#M"/>
                        </app> 
                        augentur atque omnes oppidi partes, quae minus esse firmae uidentur,
                        testudinibus ac musculis 
                        <app>
                            <!-- aptantur ω (u. BC 3.112.7-9) : temptantur Nipperdey, alii alia (u. Gaertner-Hausburg 48 n.87) -->
                            <lem wit="#ω" xml:id="aptantur-1.2">aptantur</lem>
                            <note target="#aptantur-1.2">u. <ref>BC 3.112.7-9</ref></note>
                            <rdg source="#Nipperdey" type="conjecture-corrected">
                                <corr>temptantur</corr>
                            </rdg>
                            <note target="#aptantur-1.2">alii alia (u. Gaertner-Hausburg 48 n.87)</note>
                        </app>; 
                        ex aedificiis autem per foramina in
                        proxima aedificia arietes immittuntur, quantumque aut ruinis deicitur aut
                        <app>
                            <!-- per om. STV -->
                            <lem>per</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#S #T #V"/>
                            <!-- NB: type variation-absent, but encoding pattern is unique -->
                        </app>
                        uim recipitur loci, 
                        <app>
                            <!-- in2 secl. Schneider coll. Hirt. 8.27.4 -->
                            <lem>in</lem>
                            <rdg 
                                source="#Schneider" 
                                type="conjecture-removed">
                                <surplus>in</surplus>
                            </rdg>
                            <note>u. <ptr target="https://archive.org/stream/bellumalexandri00hirtgoog#page/n12/mode/2up"/></note>
                        </app> 
                        tantum munitiones proferuntur.</seg>
                    <seg n="3">Nam 
                        <app>
                            <!-- &lt;ab&gt; Müller (cf. 61.3) -->
                            <lem source="#Müller" type="conjecture-supplied">
                                <supplied reason="omitted">ab</supplied>
                            </lem>
                            <note>cf. 61.3</note>
                        </app>
                        incendio fere tuta est
                        Alexandria, quod sine contignatione ac materia sunt aedificia 
                        <app>
                            <!-- et om. M -->
                            <lem>et</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#N"/>
                        </app>
                        structuris
                        <app>
                            <!-- ac2 MTV : et U : a S -->
                            <lem wit="#M #T #V">ac</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#U">et</rdg>
                            <rdg wit="#S">a</rdg>
                        </app>
                        fornicibus continentur tectaque sunt rudere aut pauimentis.</seg>
                    <seg n="4">Caesar maxime studebat ut quam angustissimam partem oppidi palus a
                        meridie interiecta efficiebat, hanc operibus uineisque agendis ab reliqua
                        parte urbis excluderet,</seg>
                    <seg n="5">illud 
                        <app>
                            <!-- spectans Vascosan (cf. BC 3.85.2) : expectans ω -->
                            <lem source="#Vascosan" type="conjecture-corrected">
                                <corr>spectans</corr>
                            </lem>
                            <note>cf. BC 3.85.2</note> <!-- order is significant -->
                            <rdg wit="#ω">expectans</rdg>
                        </app>
                        primum ut, cum in duas partes esset 
                        <app>
                            <!-- urbs U : ubrs M : urbis STV -->
                            <lem wit="#U">urbs</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#M">ubrs</rdg>
                            <rdg wit="#S #T #V">urbis</rdg>
                        </app>
                        diuisa, 
                        <app>
                            <!-- <sua> acies Fleischer -->
                            <lem>acies</lem>
                            <rdg source="#Fleischer">
                                <supplied reason="omitted">sua</supplied> acies
                            </rdg>
                        </app>
                        uno consilio atque imperio administraretur, deinde ut laborantibus succurri
                        atque ex altera oppidi pasrte auxilium ferri posset, in primis uero ut aqua
                        pabuloque abundaret, quarum alterius 
                        <app>
                            <!-- rei … alterius om. S (uerba 4) -->
                            <lem>rei copiam exiguam, alterius</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#S" cause="homoteleuton" type="variation-absent"/>
                        </app> 
                        nullam
                        omnino facultatem habebat; quod utrumque large palus praebere poterat.</seg>
                </p>
                <p n="2"><seg n="1">Neque uero Alexandrinis in gerendis negotiis cunctatio ulla aut
                        mora inferebatur. Nam in omnes partes, per quas fines Aegypti regnumque
                        pertinet, legatos conquisitoresque dilectus habendi causa miserant magnumque
                        numerum in oppidum telorum atque tormentorum conuexerant et innumerabilem
                        multitudinem adduxerant.</seg>
                    <seg n="2">Nec minus in urbe maximae armorum erant institutae officinae. Seruos
                        praeterea puberes armauerant; quibus domini locupletiores uictum cotidianum
                        stipendiumque praebebant.</seg>
                    <seg n="3">Hac multitudine disposita munitiones semotarum partium tuebantur;
                        ueteranas cohortes uacuas in celeberrimis urbis locis habebant, ut quacumque
                        regione pugnaretur integris uiribus ad auxilium ferendum opponi
                        possent.</seg>
                    <seg n="4">Omnibus uiis atque angiportis triplicem uallum obduxerant — erat
                        autem quadrato extructus saxo neque minus XL pedes altitudinis habebat —
                        quaeque partes urbis inferiores erant, has altissimis turribus denorum
                        tabulatorum munierant.</seg>
                    <seg n="5">Praeterea alias ambulatorias totidem tabulatorum confixerant
                        subiectisque eas rotis funibus iumentisque †obiectis† derectis plateis in
                        quamcumque erat uisum partem mouebant.</seg></p>
            </div>
